https://virtualenv.pypa.io/en/latest/

so that one can just create a virtual enviroment and enabled it

```
virtualenv venv
. ./venv/bin/activate
```

also, I suggest to put all the required packages in a `requirements.txt` file so that you can lock the version and make it easier to install. for example the `requirements.txt` file could be:

```
django==4.0.1
djangorestframework==3.13.1
django-cors-headers==3.11.0
```

and then all those dependencies can be installed just doing

```
pip install -r requirements
```', 'reactions': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/abhimantiwari/Django-AzureSQL/issues/1/reactions', 'total_count': 0, '+1': 0, '-1': 0, 'laugh': 0, 'hooray': 0, 'confused': 0, 'heart': 0, 'rocket': 0, 'eyes': 0}, 'timeline_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/abhimantiwari/Django-AzureSQL/issues/1/timeline', 'performed_via_github_app': None}}
